      <hedline>
        <hl1>Icecap Horrors</hl1>
      </hedline>
      <abstract>
        <p>Mark Steg letter on July 11 article on melting of icecap scores Americans who continue to drive gargantuan SUV's</p>
      </abstract>
    </body.head>
    <body.content>
      <block class="lead_paragraph">
        <p>To the Editor:</p>
        <p>Nero fiddled while Rome burned, just as Americans continue to drive gargantuan S.U.V.'s as the icecap melts (''Research Predicts Summer Doom for Northern Icecap,'' July 11).</p>
      </block>
      <block class="full_text">
        <p>To the Editor:</p>
        <p>Nero fiddled while Rome burned, just as Americans continue to drive gargantuan S.U.V.'s as the icecap melts (''Research Predicts Summer Doom for Northern Icecap,'' July 11).</p>
        <p>The grim future painted by Tore Furevik, the researcher, in describing ice-dwelling mammals making ''a desperate last stand'' north of Greenland is a sad and horrifying vision that should cause us to change. But it won't. When will our society espouse mature goals and values?</p>
        <p>MARK STEG  Erie, Pa.</p>
      </block>
    </body.content>
